---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }];
const lastUpdated = '20 February 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Cash Me Up"
  description="Cash Me Up privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data. UK GDPR compliant."
  noindex={true}
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
  <section class="section-padding bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm"><strong>Template Notice:</strong> This privacy policy is a template and should be reviewed by a qualified solicitor before publication. It is provided for informational purposes only.</p>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-black text-[#1B2A4A] mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none text-slate-600 space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>Cash Me Up ("we", "us", "our") operates the website cashmeup.co.uk. We are committed to protecting your personal data in accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018. For data protection enquiries, please contact us at hello@cashmeup.co.uk.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">2. What Data We Collect</h2>
          <p>We collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li><strong>Identity data:</strong> first name, last name</li>
            <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> email address, telephone number</li>
            <li><strong>Financial data:</strong> information about your car finance agreements (for PCP claims)</li>
            <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information (collected automatically)</li>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, time on site, referral source</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing preferences:</strong> your preferences regarding receiving marketing communications from us</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>To refer your PCP claim enquiry to our regulated claims management partners (legal basis: contract/consent)</li>
            <li>To register you as a member of Cash Me Up (legal basis: contract/consent)</li>
            <li>To send you marketing communications about money-saving opportunities, where you have given consent (legal basis: consent)</li>
            <li>To respond to your enquiries (legal basis: legitimate interests)</li>
            <li>To comply with our legal obligations (legal basis: legal obligation)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">4. Who We Share Your Data With</h2>
          <p>We share your personal data only with:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li><strong>Regulated claims management partners:</strong> to process your PCP claim enquiry. These partners are regulated and subject to their own data protection obligations.</li>
            <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> who help us operate our website and services (e.g. hosting providers), subject to data processing agreements.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">We do not sell your personal data to any third party.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">5. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> to request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Right to rectification:</strong> to request correction of inaccurate data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to erasure:</strong> to request deletion of your data in certain circumstances</li>
            <li><strong>Right to restrict processing</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Right to object</strong> to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
            <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> at any time, where processing is based on consent</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at hello@cashmeup.co.uk. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at ico.org.uk.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law. Member data is retained for as long as your membership is active. PCP lead data is retained for up to 7 years to comply with financial services regulations. You may request deletion at any time.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>Our website uses essential cookies necessary for the site to function, and analytical cookies to understand how visitors use the site. You can control cookies through your browser settings. A full cookie policy will be available on our website.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-4">8. Contact</h2>
          <p>For any privacy-related queries, please contact us at hello@cashmeup.co.uk or via our <a href="/contact/" class="text-[#2D6B2D] hover:underline">Contact page</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
